.TH "clkdm_allow_idle_nolock" 9 "clkdm_allow_idle_nolock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clkdm_allow_idle_nolock \- enable hwsup idle transitions for clkdm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clkdm_allow_idle_nolock
.BI "(struct clockdomain *clkdm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clkdm" 12
struct clockdomain *
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allow the hardware to automatically switch the clockdomain \fIclkdm\fP
into active or idle states, as needed by downstream clocks.  If the
clockdomain has any downstream clocks enabled in the clock
framework, wkdep/sleepdep autodependencies are added; this is so
device drivers can read and write to the device.  Only for use by
the powerdomain code.  No return value.
